s/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utiriantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirian Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/iconsg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 3:31:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirianicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which cloak to use</span><hr size=1> If weight is an issue, the White Bear gives you 15 more stones than the Seahorse does.  (+5 STR and it weights 10 stones less)  That's one of the reasons I'm using it, I'm always encumbered.  If I wasn't, I'm not sure which I'd choose, but the weight factor gave my current decision easy. <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 3:57:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valya.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which cloak to use</span><hr size=1> I have both of the 2 you are debating.  I currently use the white bear pelt cloak pretty much all the time. But I self buff at just about 1200AC even with the white bear pelt cloak, which currently makes me content.  I would ditch both in a heartbeat for a Lodizal or Massive Underbulk, of course.<br><br>A while back (about when I broke 1100AC self buffed) I started choosing HP and, to some extent, WIS gear even at the cost of some AC in a number of slots. So my Symbol of Marr lives in the bank while I use my Karkona's Talisman, for instance; and I use an Ice Forged Shackle instead of a Deepwater Bracer; and like that.   I'm still not thrilled with my HP and WIS but they are getting there  (145 WIS as a half elf in my AC gear is almost respectable, hehe).<br><br>My haste is in my waist slot btw, that may have been the point of the question about what was in your waist slot. Since you use the Axgorath I assume you have haste on your gauntlets or elsewhere? <p><font size="+1">	<a href="http://www.geocities.com/valya_w" target="_blank"><b><u>Valya Wanderfoot </u></b></a>, </font><br>60 Crusader<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94293">Magelo Profile</a><br>Melliasan Sforzanda, 41 Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95676">Magelo profile</a><br>Mithaniel Marr</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A> at: 3/8/02 3:59:53 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=172.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=172.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=7><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToF